tion%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20339px)%2085vw%2C%20339px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22339%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742.jpg%20838w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742-210x300.jpg%20210w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742-715x1024.jpg%20715w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-682410%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22485%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEarlier%20soldiers%20were%20paid%20in%20salt%20instead%20of%20money%20as%20salary%2C%20it%20is%20said.%20Back%20then%20agriculture%20and%20animal%20husbandry%20had%20developed%20so%20much%20that%20produce%20often%20became%20surplus.%20But%20since%20salt%20cultivation%20was%20not%20possible%20for%20traditional%20agriculturalists%2C%20they%20used%20to%20work%20to%20earn%20salt.%20Salt%20signifies%20loyalty%20in%20some%20Hindi%20idioms%20even%20today.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELegend%20has%20it%20that%20soldiers%20were%20paid%20in%20salt%20in%20the%20Roman%20civilisation%20also.%20It%20is%20also%20claimed%20that%20the%20word%20soldier%20itself%20originates%20from%20the%20Roman%20word%20%E2%80%98saldare%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20means%20%E2%80%98to%20give%20salt%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20in%20our%20own%20country%2C%20Noniyas%20are%20counted%20among%20Vaishya%20communities%20today.%20The%20word%20Vaishya%20evokes%20a%20kind%20of%20business%20where%20goods%20produced%20through%20labour%20are%20purchased%20at%20a%20lower%20price%20and%20sold%20at%20a%20higher%20price.%20However%2C%20Noniya%20are%20labourers%20themselves.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20people%20of%20Noniya%20caste%20produced%20salt%20and%20made%20it%20available%20to%20people.%20More%20than%20business%20it%20was%20art%20for%20them%20%E2%80%93%20art%20which%20was%20directly%20linked%20to%20the%20soil.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETheir%20association%20with%20soil%20is%20similar%20to%20that%20of%20farmers%20who%20grow%20grains.%20Often%2C%20in%20exchange%20for%20salt%2C%20farmers%20would%20give%20them%20grains.%20It%20is%20possible%20that%20an%20unjust%20system%20imposed%20the%20label%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ebaniya%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%93%20businesspersons%20%E2%80%93%20on%20them%2C%20alleging%20that%20they%20take%20ten%20pounds%20of%20grain%20for%20a%20pinch%20of%20salt.%20But%20what%20do%20people%20know%20about%20the%20labour%20they%20undertook%20to%20produce%20a%20pinch%20of%20salt%3F%20The%20process%20involved%20scanning%20the%20land%20for%20anthills%2C%20collecting%20soil%20from%20there%20and%20extracting%20salt%20from%20it.%20Since%20this%20soil%20is%20also%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Enon%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20they%20came%20to%20be%20referred%20to%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Enoniya%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20some%20places%20they%20are%20also%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Elonia%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20There%20is%20also%20a%20sub-caste%20called%20Noniya%20Chauhan%20who%20according%20to%20some%20are%20the%20descendants%20of%20Prithviraj%20Chauhan.%20While%20this%20is%20unconfirmed%20information%2C%20the%20fact%20is%20that%20they%20were%20master%20chemical%20engineers%2C%20who%20made%20saltpetre%2C%20acid%20and%20sulfur.%20The%20word%20Lonia%20is%20derived%20from%20the%20Sanskrit%20word%20for%20salt%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Elavan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20But%20socially%20this%20group%20was%20labelled%20Shudra.%20Even%20though%20everybody%20eats%20the%20salt%20they%20produce%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98upper%20classes%E2%80%99%20do%20not%20want%20to%20share%20spaces%20with%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESalt%20production%20is%20not%20their%20only%20contribution.%20Like%20Tilka%20Manjhi%20and%20Sido-Kanho%2C%20they%20led%20an%20armed%20rebellion%20against%20the%20British%20government%20that%20continued%20for%2030%20years%20around%201750.%20Hajipur%2C%20Tirhut%2C%20Saran%20and%20Purnia%20of%20Bihar%20were%20the%20main%20centres%20of%20saltpetre%20production%20and%20they%20led%20this%20rebellion%20there.%20However%2C%20the%20British%20started%20trading%20in%20salt%20and%20began%20persecuting%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20British%20had%20opened%20a%20saltpetre%20factory%20in%20Chhapra%20district%20of%20Bihar%2C%20which%20was%20looted%20by%20rebels%20of%20the%20Noniya%20caste%20in%201771.%20The%20factory%20was%20set%20on%20fire.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBefore%20Mangal%20Pandey%20was%20Budhu%20Noniya%2C%20who%20rose%20up%20against%20the%20British%20and%20gave%20a%20tough%20fight.%20He%20was%20born%20in%20Karpura%20village%20of%20Begusarai.%20Legend%20has%20it%20that%20after%20his%20capture%20by%20British%20soldiers%2C%20he%20was%20killed%20by%20being%20thrown%20into%20a%20cauldron%20of%20smoldering%20salt.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELater%2C%20Gandhi%20also%20had%20Mukutdhari%20Prasad%20Chauhan%20as%20his%20ally%2C%20who%20hailed%20from%20the%20Noniya%20caste.%20Even%20though%20Rajkumar%20Shukla%20was%20not%20as%20close%20to%20Gandhi%20as%20Mukutdhari%20in%20Champaran%20in%201917%2C%20only%20Shukla%20finds%20mention%20in%20historical%20records.%20One%20might%20ask%20%E2%80%93%20is%20this%20not%20evidence%20of%20how%20historiography%20is%20influenced%20by%20caste%20discrimination%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20people%20of%20Noniya%20caste%20are%20still%20there%20and%20their%20population%20in%20Bihar%20(according%20to%20the%20caste-based%20census%20report%20of%202022)%20is%202%2C498%2C474.%20At%20the%20government%20level%2C%20they%20have%20been%20included%20in%20the%20extremely%20backward%20class.%20But%20socially%2C%20they%20are%20still%20considered%20%E2%80%98untouchable.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETranslated%20from%20Hindi%20by%20Naushin%20Rehman.%20Read%20the%20Hindi%20original%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewirehindi.com%2F263536%2Fbihar-caste-survey-nonia-caste-society%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERead%20earlier%20parts%20of%20the%20series%20on%20the%20following%20communities%20by%20clicking%20on%20their%20names%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-ghasi%5C%22%3EGhasi%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-santrash%5C%22%3ESantrash%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-santrash%5C%22%3EMadaria%3C%2Fa%3E%20%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-koeri-kushwaha%5C%22%3EKoeri%2FKushwaha%3C%2Fa%3E%20%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-chaupal%5C%22%3EChaupal%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-nai-hajjaam%5C%22%3ENai%2FHajjaam%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-pasi%5C%22%3EPasi%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-rangrez%5C%22%3ERangrez%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-chamar%5C%22%3ECha