B%20and%20claimed%20the%20implant%20would%20eventually%20%26quot%3Bsolve%26quot%3B%20conditions%20including%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-said-neuralink-could-solve-autism-and-schizophrenia-2019-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eautism%20and%20schizophrenia%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider's%20Hilary%20Brueck%20reported%20in%202091%20that%20neuroscientists%20believe%20Neuralink%20won't%20likely%20be%20able%20to%20%26quot%3Bsolve%26quot%3B%20mental%20health%20conditions%20or%20change%20the%20developmental%20architecture%20of%20the%20brain%20when%20it%20is%20impacted%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-neuralink-wont-solve-autism-schizophrenia-2019-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ediseases%20like%20Alzheimer's%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20the%20technology%20may%20be%20effective%20at%20stimulating%20electrodes%2C%20thereby%20helping%20paralyzed%20patients%20achieve%20better%20mobility%20or%20helping%20blind%20patients%20to%20see.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20Neuralink%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EYears%20in%20the%20making%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20billionaire%20Tesla%20and%20SpaceX%20CEO%20has%20been%20promising%20that%20Neuralink%20would%20soon%20begin%20testing%20on%20humans%20since%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FDA%20initially%20rejected%20Neuralink's%20request%20for%20approval%20to%20test%20its%20brain%20chips%20in%20humans%20last%20March%2C%20citing%20concerns%20that%20it%20could%20overheat%20or%20move%20in%20the%20brain%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Finvestigates%2Fspecial-report%2Fneuralink-musk-fda%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EReuters%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%20Approval%20was%20ultimately%20granted%20in%20May%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20approval%20prompted%20thousands%20of%20prospective%20patients%20to%20sign%20up%20as%20volunteers%20to%20have%20a%20portion%20of%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-neuralink-human-trial-patient-elon-musk-brain-implant-report-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eskull%20removed%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20implant%20inserted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20company%20began%20recruiting%20for%20its%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-apply-for-neuralink-human-trial-study-requirements-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efirst%20human%20trial%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20September%2C%20Neuralink%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fneuralink.com%2Fblog%2Ffirst-clinical-trial-open-for-recruitment%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eblog%20post%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20was%20seeking%20patients%20with%20spinal%20cord%20injuries%20who%20have%20paralysis%20in%20all%20four%20limbs%20or%20who%20have%20been%20diagnosed%20with%20amyotrophic%20lateral%20sclerosis%2C%20also%20known%20as%20Lou%20Gehrig's%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Neuralink%20says%20it%20hopes%20to%20help%20people%20with%20neurological%20disorders%20with%20its%20implanted%20devices%2C%20the%20company%20also%20aims%20to%20eventually%20develop%20an%20implant%20that%20will%20allow%20people%20to%20send%20messages%20or%20play%20games%20using%20only%20their%20thoughts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%2C%20who%20in%202022%20claimed%20he%20plans%20to%20implant%20one%20of%20the%20chips%20in%20his%20own%20brain%20someday%2C%20has%20said%20he%20aims%20to%20create%20such%20a%20powerful%20interface%20through%20Neuralink%20that%20it%20will%20enable%20humans%20to%20process%20information%20faster%2C%20speed%20up%20cognition%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bachieve%20a%20sort%20of%20symbiosis%20with%20artificial%20intelligence.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20some%20experts%20are%20skeptical.%20In%202019%2C%20Business%20Insider's%20Brueck%20spoke%20to%20Columbia%20University%20neuroscientist%20Randy%20Bruno%2C%20who%20said%20he%20was%20unsure%20that%20Neuralink%20could%20ever%20facilitate%20such%20super-enhanced%20thinking%20power%20due%20to%20the%20basic%20function%20of%20the%20brain.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNeurons%20work%20at%20a%20certain%20speed%2C%26quot%3B%20Bruno%2C%20a%20researcher%20who%20implants%20probes%20into%20mouse%20brains%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20that's%20ultimately%20going%20to%20be%20limiting.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20have%20raised%20concerns%20over%20the%20ethics%20of%20the%20technology%20and%20its%20development%2C%20and%20Musk's%20promises%20about%20what%20Neuralink%20will%20be%20able%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20should%2C%20of%20course%2C%20hope%20that%20the%20intervention%20ultimately%20functions%20as%20advertised%20with%20few%20potential%20adverse%20side-effects%2C%26quot%3B%20Jason%20T.%20Eberl%2C%20professor%20and%20director%20of%20the%20Albert%20Gnaegi%20Center%20for%20Health%20Care%20Ethics%20at%20Saint%20Louis%20University%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.healthline.com%2Fhealth-news%2Fwhy-experts-are-skeptical-of-elon-musks-brain-implants%23Neuralink-clinical-trials-not-yet-started%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHealthline%20in%202022%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20any%20for-profit%20medical%20device%20company%20also%20has%20a%20vested%20interest%20in%20generating%20a%20consumer%20base%2C%20which%20is%20why%20they%20make%20the%20sometimes%20grandiose%20claims%20they%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20you%20filled%20out%20an%20application%20for%20Neuralink's%20human%20trials%2C%20or%20do%20you%20have%20a%20tip%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20gkay%40insider.com%20from%20a%20nonwork%20email.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fel