r%20Coco%20Cr%C3%A8me%20shampoo%20is%20sulfate-free%20and%20softens%20the%20strands%20as%20it%20cleanses.%20The%20formula%20does%20contain%20silicones%20although%20they're%20water-soluble%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20they%20should%20wash%20away%20after%20shampooing%20instead%20of%20leaving%20residue%20over%20the%20hair.%20The%20pump%20handle%20makes%20it%20easier%20to%20portion%20the%20right%20amount%20of%20product%2C%20and%20curly%20hair%20types%20will%20only%20need%20a%20small%20amount%20(usually%20a%20quarter-sized)%20to%20lather%20and%20cleanse%20the%20entire%20mane.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20anti-breakage%3A%20TGIN%20Miracle%20RepairRX%20Shampoo%3Cp%3EThank%20God%20It's%20Natural%20was%20created%20by%20the%20late%20Chris-Tia%20Donaldson%2C%20who%20graduated%20from%20Harvard%20Law%20School%20and%20then%20transitioned%20her%20career%20from%20law%20to%20beauty.%20Her%20natural%20haircare%20products%20are%20Insider-approved%20and%20come%20in%20three%20lines%20tailored%20to%20different%20needs.%20The%20Miracle%20RepairRX%20shampoo%20is%20specifically%20formulated%20to%20cleanse%20the%20hair%20gently%20and%20strengthen%20it%20with%20biotin%2C%20castor%20oil%2C%20and%20honey%2C%20making%20it%20ideal%20for%20hair%20dealing%20with%20breakage.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERead%20our%20full%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fthank-god-its-natural-haircare-review%5C%22%3EThank%20God%20It's%20Natural%20haircare%20review%3C%2Fa%3E%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20natural%20option%3A%20Sienna%20Naturals%20H.A.P.I.%20Shampoo%3Cp%3EIssa%20Rae%20doesn't%20just%20make%20award-winning%20TV%20shows%2C%20but%20she%20makes%20incredible%20hair%20products%20as%20the%20co-owner%20of%20Sienna%20Naturals%20with%20Hannah%20Diop.%20This%20shampoo's%20superpower%20is%20its%20mix%20of%20aloe%2C%20baobab%2C%20and%20lavender%20oil%2C%20making%20it%20smell%20as%20good%20as%20it%20cleans.%20Sienna%20Naturals%20products%20are%20vegan%20and%20synthetic%20fragrance-free%2C%20which%20is%20especially%20helpful%20if%20you%20have%20sensitive%20skin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ETypes%20of%20curly%20hair%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223334%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Graphic%20showing%20different%20Curl%20Types%20of%20Type%203%20Curly%20hair%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F602c09102edd0f001a8d5eb0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221687%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EAlyssa%20Powell%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20main%20hair%20types%20of%20curly%20hair.%20Type%203%20includes%20loose%20to%20medium%20tight%20curls%2C%20and%20type%204%20includes%20tight%20to%20super%20tight%20curls%20and%20coils.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223334%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Graphic%20displaying%20Curl%20Types%20of%20Type%204%20Coily%20hair%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F605e12b08f71c3001853a838%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EAlyssa%20Powell%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20folks%20will%20stress%20hair%20typing%20when%20you're%20looking%20for%20the%20right%20product%20for%20you.%20The%20difference%20between%20curly%20(3A%2C%203B%2C%20and%203C%20type%20patterns)%20and%20coily%20hair%20(4A%2C%204B%2C%20and%204C%20type%20patterns)%20is%20how%20tight%20and%20defined%20your%20ringlets%20are.%20While%20the%20hair%20typing%20system%20can%20be%20helpful%2C%20it%20also%20misses%20the%20mark%20since%20it%20doesn't%20capture%20all%20the%20other%20important%20aspects%20of%20your%20hair%20like%20texture%2C%20density%2C%20and%20elasticity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EIngredients%20to%20look%20for%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20as%20ingredients%20go%2C%20you%20want%20to%20look%20out%20for%20parabens%2C%20isopropyl%20alcohol%2C%20mineral%20oil%2C%20silicones%2C%20and%20artificial%20dyes%2C%20as%20they%20can%20dry%20out%20and%20damage%20your%20delicate%20hair.%20And%20although%20you%20may%20have%20heard%20negative%20things%20about%20sulfates%20%E2%80%94%20a%20detergent%20found%20in%20cleaning%20products%2C%20body%20wash%2C%20and%20haircare%20%E2%80%94%20certified%20trichologist%20Dr.%20Kari%20Williams%20doesn't%20think%20they're%20all%20bad.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%5BSulfates%5D%20are%20designed%20to%20strip%20things%20of%20oil%20and%20dirt%20and%20to%20break%20it%20down%2C%20so%20they%20are%20effective%20in%20shampoos%20for%20that%20reason%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20Williams%20explains.%20In%20her%20opinion%2C%20sulfates%20aren't%20damaging%20when%20they're%20used%20occasionally%20versus%20daily.%20%26quot%3BIf%20your%20hair%20is%20filthy%2C%20and%20you%20don't%20wash%20your%20hair%20that%20frequently%2C%20then%20you%20actually%20need%20sulfates.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fbest-conditioners-for-curly-hair%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERead%20more%20about%20how%20to%20care%20for%20curly%20hair%20here%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EFAQs%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20does%20curly%20hair%20need%20special%20shampoo%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ECurly%20hair%20needs%20different%20things%20than%20straight%20hair%20from%20shampoo.%20Here's%20why%3A%20sebum%20is%20the%20natural%20oil%20our%20scalps%20produce.%20Curls%20slow%20down%20how%20fast%20that%20oil%20travels%20down%20our%20hair.%20Because%20of%20this%2C%20curly%20hair%20thrives%20from%20a%20shampoo%20that%20cleanses%20the%20scalp%20without%20stripping%20the%20hair%20of%20its%20needed%20moisture.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20why%20most%20curly%20shampoos%20have%20moisturizing%20ingredients%20as%20well%20as%20cleansing%20ones.%20On%20top%20of%20that%2C%20it's%20helpful%20to%20avoid%20harsh%20chemicals%20that%20may%20cause%20scalp%20irritation%20like%20synthetic%20fragrances%2C%20especially%20when%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20at%20a%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20often%20should%20curly%20hair%20be%20washed%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20often%20you%20wash%20your%20curly%20hair%20depends%20on%20how%20quickly%20your%20hair%20gets%20oily.%20Curly%20hair%20takes%20longer%20than%20straight%20hair%2C%20for%20example%2C%20to%20get%20oily.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%2C%20it's%20better%20to%20wait%20a%20few%20weeks%20in%20between%20washing.%20This%20is%20all%20to%20say%2C%20develop%20your%20wash%20schedule%20based%20on%20your%20hair.%20If%20you%20want%20to%20refresh%20in%20between%20washes%2C%20you%20can%20co-wash%20or%20rinse%20with%20plain%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20it%20better%20to%20wash%20curly%20hair%20at%20night%20or%20in%20the%20morning%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20right%20or%20wrong%20answer%20for%20this%20because%20it%20depends%20on%20the%20drying%20time.%20Ideally%2C%20after%20doing%20your%20wash%20routine%20and%20styling%2C%20there's%20time%20for%20your%20hair%20to%20dry.%20Since%20wash%20routines%20can%20take%20a%20few%20hours%2C%20it's%20probably%20best%20to%20start%20earlier%20than%20later%20since%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20sleep%20with%20a%20head%20full%20of%20cold%2C%20wet%20hair.%20There's%20also%20a%20bonus%20with%20washing%20in%20the%20morning%3A%20You%20get%20a%20whole%20day%20to%20flaunt%20your%20fresh%2C%20day%20one%20curls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EIs%20it%20better%20to%20wash%20curly%20hair%20with%20hot%20or%20cold%20water%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20you%20should%20wash%20curly%20hair%20at%20whatever%20temperature%20you're%20most%20comfortable%20with%2C%20Aeleise%20Ollarvia%2C%20curly%20hair%20expert%20and%20CEO%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fcutitkinky%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECut%20It%20Kinky%3C%2Fa%3E%20confirms.%20However%2C%20Ollarvia%20shares%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20a%20vibrant%20color%2C%20always%20wash%20with%20cold%20%5Bwater%5D%20because%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20lose%20the%20color%20of%20the%20dye.%26quot%3B%20An%20important%20aspect%20of%20cleansing%20curly%20hair%20with%20shampoo%20is%20ensuring%20all%20the%20product%20is%20rinsed%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20water%20temperature.%20Be%20sure%20to%20rinse%20your%20curly%20or%20coily%20strands%20with%20enough%20water%20to%20eliminate%20hair%20(and%20scalp)%20dehydration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3ECan%20you%20wash%20curly%20hair%20with%20just%20conditioner%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ETechnically%2C%20you%20can't%20use%20just%20conditioner%20to%20wash%20your%20hair.%20Ollarvia%20confirms%20that%20while%20there%20are%20some%20shampoos%20designed%20to%20add%20moisture%20(like%20a%20co-wash%20or%20moisturizing%20shampoo)%2C%20the%20job%20of%20a%20curly%20shampoo%20is%20to%20cleanse%20the%20scalp%20and%20hair%2C%20while%20a%20curly%20conditioner%20rehydrates%20and%20adds%20moisture.%20Sometimes%2C%20those%20with%20curly%20hair%20will%20condition%20before%20shampooing%20for%20easier%20detangling%2C%20but%20curly%20hair%20(like%20all%20hair)%20needs%20to%20be%20cleansed%20to%20rid%20hair%20of%20buildup%20from%20product%2C%20sweat%2C%20or%20oil.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fbest-shampoos-for-curly-hair%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706568761000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b7fd0bac2de4f17ee58a4d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fbest-shampoos-for-curly-hair%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Tired%20of%20haircare%20that%20isn't%20tailored%20to%20your%20curly%20hair%20needs%3F%20We%20rounded%20up%20the%20best%20shampoos%20for%20curly%20hair%20in%202024%2C%20whether%20you%20have%20loose%20curls%20or%20tight%20coils.%22%2C%22author%22