E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Eshoddy%20North%20Korean%20ammunition%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20But%20these%20North%20Korean%20ballistic%20missiles%20are%20not%20some%20knockoff%20of%20the%20notorious%201950s%20Soviet%20Scud%2C%20a%20liquid-fueled%20rocket%20that%20takes%20more%20than%20an%20hour%20to%20launch.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmissilethreat.csis.org%2Fmissile%2Fkn-23%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3EKn-23%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20with%20an%20estimated%20range%20of%20up%20to%20500%20miles%20and%20a%20one-ton%20warhead%2C%20bears%20some%20resemblance%20to%20Russia's%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmissiledefenseadvocacy.org%2Fmissile-threat-and-proliferation%2Ftodays-missile-threat%2Frussia%2Fiskander-m-ss-26%2F%255d%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3ESS-26%20Iskander%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20SRBM.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmissilethreat.csis.org%2Fmissile%2Fkn-24%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3EKn-24%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20with%20a%20range%20of%20250%20miles%20and%20a%20one-ton%20warhead%2C%20looks%20like%20a%20US%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmissilethreat.csis.org%2Fmissile%2Fatacms%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3EATACMS%20missile%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThese%20are%20more%20sophisticated%2C%20solid-fueled%20missiles%20that%20can%20be%20launched%20without%20much%20preparation%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Masao%20Dahlgren%2C%20a%20missile%20defense%20expert%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThey%20may%20have%20some%20design%20heritage%20with%20Russian%20systems%2C%20but%20they%20borrow%20heavily%20from%20North%20Korean%20expertise.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20world%20has%20tended%20to%20focus%20on%20North%20Korea's%20ICBM%20and%20nuclear%20weapons%20programs%2C%20which%20may%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20hit%20the%20United%20States%20with%20an%20atomic%20weapon.%20Short-range%20ballistic%20missiles%20have%20received%20less%20attention%2C%20weapons%20that%20could%20target%20South%20Korea%20command%20centers%20and%20US%20bases%20and%20ships.%20%26quot%3BThese%20theater-range%20missiles%20are%20often%20overlooked%2C%26quot%3B%20Dahlgren%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20hasn't%20been%20enough%20focus%20on%20these%20shorter-range%20missiles%20that%20North%20Korea%20and%20Iran%20are%20exporting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20North%20Korean%20SRBMs%20are%20used%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20knowledge%20of%20their%20capabilities%20will%20grow%20from%20analysis%20of%20impact%20sites%20and%20missile%20debris.%20But%20for%20now%2C%20not%20much%20is%20known%20about%20their%20capabilities%2C%20especially%20their%20accuracy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThe%20real%20secret%20sauce%26quot%3B%20will%20be%20learning%20about%20their%20guidance%20systems%2C%20Dahlgren%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20hope%20to%20learn%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20from%20parts%20that%20the%20Ukrainians%20will%20be%20picking%20up%20in%20the%20next%20couple%20of%20months.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOlder%20ballistic%20missiles%20like%20the%20Scud%2C%20and%20its%20ancestor%20the%20Nazi%20V-2%2C%20were%20area%20bombardment%20weapons%20that%20might%20land%20within%20a%20couple%20of%20miles%20of%20the%20target.%20However%2C%20Dahlgren%20believes%20that%20North%20Korean%20SRBMs%20could%20be%20accurate%20enough%20to%20hit%20pinpoint%20targets%2C%20just%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F01%2F18%2Fworld%2Fmiddleeast%2Firan-missile-program.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3EIranian%20missiles%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20did%20during%20recent%20strikes%20in%20Iraq%2C%20Pakistan%20and%20Syria.%20%26quot%3BI%20wouldn't%20underestimate%20North%20Korea's%20capability%20to%20make%20tactically%20relevant%20systems%20that%20could%20strike%20at%20military%20targets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20for%20Moscow%2C%20quantity%20may%20be%20more%20important%20than%20quality.%20To%20compensate%20for%20the%20poor%20performance%20of%20its%20ground%20troops%20and%20air%20force%2C%20Russia%20has%20expended%20vast%20quantities%20of%20guided%20missiles%20and%20artillery%20shells%2C%20so%20far%20without%20decisive%20effect.%20This%20suggests%20that%20Russia%20will%20need%20a%20lot%20of%20North%20Korean%20missiles%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20raises%20the%20question%20of%20North%20Korea's%20rocket%20manufacturing%20capacity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThere%20have%20been%20numbers%20thrown%20all%20over%20the%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dahlgren.%20%26quot%3BThe%20problem%20here%20is%20that%20North%20Korea%20has%20substantially%20advanced%20the%20state%20of%20its%20production%20base%20as%20of%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20months.%26quot%3B%20In%202023%2C%20the%20International%20Institute%20for%20Strategic%20Studies%20estimated%20that%20North%20Korea%20has%20built%20a%20dozen%20ICBMs%20and%20intermediate-range%20missiles%20apiece%2C%20plus%20at%20least%2070%20SRBMs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20worry%20for%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20US%2C%20Japan%20and%20South%20Korea%20%E2%80%93%20is%20what%20Pyongyang%20will%20get%20from%20Moscow%20in%20return%20for%20missiles.%20Payment%20could%20include%20money%20for%20the%20cash-strapped%20regime%2C%20food%20or%20weapons%20such%20as%20advanced%20jets.%20But%20Russia%20could%20also%20turn%20over%20missile%20designs%20and%20components%2C%20such%20as%20for%20hypersonic%20weapons.%20For%20the%20Kremlin%2C%20this%20would%20mean%20a%20chance%20to%20import%20more%20missiles%