h%20a%20public%20man%2C%20debating%2C%20acting%2C%20becoming%20president%20of%20the%20Wodehouse%20Society%20and%20of%20the%20Quiz%20Club%20before%20being%20elected%20president%20of%20the%20College%20Union.%20He%20was%20charming%20and%20outgoing%2C%20but%2C%20from%20the%20start%2C%20ferociously%20ambitious.%20Shashi%20wanted%20to%20make%20a%20mark%20in%20the%20world%2C%20quicker%20and%20more%20dramatically%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethan%20any%20Stephanian%20(or%20perhaps%20any%20Indian)%20before%20him.%20Whereas%20Rukun%20had%20no%20ambition%20to%20become%20well%20known.%20In%20college%2C%20all%20he%20wanted%20to%20do%20was%20read%2C%20listen%20to%20music%2C%20and%20have%20one-on-one%20conversations%20with%20friends.%20In%20the%20OUP%2C%20all%20he%20wanted%20to%20do%20was%20edit%20books%3B%20while%20he%20gloried%20in%20the%20success%20of%20his%20authors%2C%20he%20never%20remotely%20wanted%20to%20take%20any%20credit%20for%20this.%20As%20we%20have%20seen%2C%20this%20inwardness%20and%20reclusiveness%20deepened%20even%20further%20when%20he%20retreated%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ERanikhet%20and%20ran%20Permanent%20Black%20from%20there.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20328px)%2085vw%2C%20328px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29164317%2FCooking-of-Books-HR-1.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22328%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29164317%2FCooking-of-Books-HR-1.jpeg%20782w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29164317%2FCooking-of-Books-HR-1-196x300.jpeg%20196w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29164317%2FCooking-of-Books-HR-1-667x1024.jpeg%20667w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-694831%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22503%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98The%20Cooking%20of%20Books%2C%E2%80%99%20Ramachandra%20Guha%2C%20Juggernaut%2C%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERukun%20had%20a%20mixed%20opinion%20of%20Shashi%20Tharoor%20as%20a%20writer%2C%20and%20as%20a%20public%20figure.%20Of%20Tharoor%E2%80%98s%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Great%20Indian%20Novel%3C%2Fem%3E%20he%20once%20wrote%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%5BT%5Dhe%20deliberately%20provocative%20immodesty%20of%20the%20title%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eactually%20has%20less%20to%20with%20the%20author%E2%80%99s%20nearly%20incredible%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eself-esteem%20than%20with%20the%20irreverent%2C%20daring%20and%20heady%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eatmosphere%20of%20the%20St.%20Stephen%E2%80%99s%20to%20which%20this%20over-spun%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eallegory%20seems%20completely%20traceable.%20The%20proper%20place%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Efor%20this%20novel%20to%20have%20been%20serialized%20was%20%3Cem%3EKooler%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3ETalk%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EStephanian%20rag%20made%20up%20of%20wit%2C%20puns%2C%20good%20humour%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Esatire%20and%20irreverence.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20that%20same%20essay%2C%20Rukun%20compared%20Tharoor%20unfavourably%20to%20other%20novelists%20from%20St.%20Stephen%E2%80%99s.%20Whereas%20the%20language%20of%20Upamanyu%20Chatterjee%2C%20was%2C%20he%20thought%2C%20%E2%80%98a%20very%20much%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Emore%20refined%20and%20reflective%20version%E2%80%99%20of%20Kooler%20Talk%2C%20both%20%E2%80%98Allan%20Sealy%20and%20Amitav%20Ghosh%20are%20traceable%20to%20St.%20Stephen%E2%80%99s%20much%20less%20easily%20and%20much%20more%20obscurely%20than%20Tharoor%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20Chatterjee%E2%80%99.%20While%20taking%20something%20from%20their%20old%20college%2C%20these%20more%20gifted%20writers%20had%20outgrown%20its%20milieu%2C%20tackling%20complex%20historical%20and%20moral%20questions%20beyond%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20grasp%20of%20the%20common%20or%20garden%20variety%20of%20Stephanian%20novelist.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20is%20well%20known%2C%20after%20St.%20Stephen%E2%80%99s%2C%20Shashi%20Tharoor%20went%20on%20to%20a%20long%20and%20distinguished%20career%20at%20the%20United%20Nations%2C%20before%20returning%20to%20India%20to%20enter%20politics%20and%20joining%20the%20Congress%20Party.%20He%20became%20a%20member%20of%20Parliament%2C%20then%20a%20Union%20minister%2C%20before%20being%20sacked%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ein%20part%20because%20of%20a%20jokey%20tweet%2C%20and%20in%20part%20because%20he%20seemed%20keener%20in%20involving%20himself%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20foremost%20cricket%20tournament%2C%20the%20IPL%20(Indian%20Premier%20League)%2C%20than%20in%20discharging%20his%20responsibilities%20as%20a%20minister.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20Tharoor%20was%20asked%20to%20resign%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20Rukun%20wrote%20me%20a%20mail%20combining%20compassion%20with%20sarcasm%2C%20which%20must%20%E2%80%93%20only%20slightly%20redacted%20%E2%80%93%20now%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ebe%20made%20public%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20feel%20a%20bit%20sorry%20for%20him.%20So%20much%20ambition%2C%20and%20successful%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eall%20the%20way%20till%20the%20failed%20attempt%20to%20become%20UN%20chief.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20now%20the%20first%20big%20political%20victim%20of%20something%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Esilly%20as%20a%20Tweet.%20Poetic%20justice%20I%20guess%20for%20former%20editor%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eof%20that%20expanded%20version%20of%20tweeting%2C%20Kooler%20Talk.%20He%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ecompletely%20secular%20and%20personally%20decent%2C%20a%20good%20man%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Efallen%20among%20thieves.%20Since%20he%20has%20literary%20ambition%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eas%20well%2C%20a%20good%20analogy%20seems%20Tharoor%20as%20Macbeth%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ewith%20vaulting%20ambition%20.%20.%20.%20trying%20to%20dethrone%20King%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ELalit%20Duncan%20Modi%20and%20coming%20a%20cropper.%20But%20I%20fear%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Esomething%20worse%20is%20going%20to%20befall%20us%20now%3A%20he%20will%20inflict%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ehis%20third-rate%20narcissistic%20journalism%20on%20us%20once%20again.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20should%20plead%20with%20Nirmala%20Lakshman%20%5Beditor%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EHindu%20Sunday%20Magazine%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20where%20Tharoor%20had%20a%20column%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ebefore%20he%20joined%20politics%5D%20to%20run%20for%20her%20life%20before%20he%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Estarts%20badgering%20her.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShashi%20Tharoor%20and%20Rukun%20Advani%20were%20exact%20contemporaries%20at%20St.%20Stephen%E2%80%99s.%20Superficially%2C%20they%20were%20alike%3B%20both%20brilliant%2C%20both%20very%20widely%20read%2C%20each%20far%20removed%20in%20his%20interests%20from%20the%20%E2%80%98sports%20type%E2%80%99%20that%20I%20myself%20was%20in%20college.%20Even%20some%20of%20their%20literary%20tastes%20overlapped%3B%20both%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eadmired%20Wodehouse%20and%20Orwell%2C%20for%20example.%20Yet%20in%20terms%20of%20character%20and%20personality%20no%20two%20Stephanians%20could%20be%20so%20radically%20dissimilar.%20I%20suspect%20most%20readers%20of%20this%20book%20will%20know%20Shashi%20Tharoor%E2%80%99s%20public%20profile.%20To%20show%20how%20Rukun%20Advani%20is%2C%20as%20it%20were%2C%20his%20absolute%20Other%2C%20I%20must%20take%20recourse%20to%20the%20words%20of%20the%20most%20gifted%20of%20all%20Stephanian%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eprose%20stylists%2C%20Mukul%20Kesavan%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%5BRukun%5D%20has%20no%20interest%20in%20impressing%20others.%20This%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Esounds%20impressive%20but%20it%20isn%E2%80%99t%20because%20this%20freedom%20from%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ehuman%20neediness%20isn%E2%80%99t%20down%20to%20modesty%2