f%20relatives.%20The%20legacy%20of%20starvation%20was%20never%20far%20from%20the%20surface.%20Food%20was%20used%20to%20soothe.%20There%20was%20no%20waste.%20Her%20grandfather%20finished%20every%20crumb%20from%20every%20plate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20impact%20the%20Holocaust%20has%20had%20through%20the%20generations%20runs%20deep.%20Quite%20how%20we%20remember%20the%20past%20and%20its%20legacy%20varies%20hugely.%20Cohen%20is%20one%20of%20a%20small%20but%20growing%20number%20of%20the%20children%20and%20grandchildren%20of%20Holocaust%20survivors%20who%20have%20replicated%20the%20Auschwitz%20death%20camp%20tattoo%20on%20their%20own%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Felie-wiesel-survived-auschwitz-to-give-us-a-vivid-glimpse-of-the-kingdom-of-night-62024%5C%22%3EAuschwitz%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20Nazi-occupied%20Poland%2C%20was%20the%20only%20camp%20where%20numbers%20were%20tattooed%20on%20those%20inmates%20not%20selected%20for%20immediate%20death.%20In%20replacing%20the%20person%E2%80%99s%20name%2C%20this%20number%20has%20become%20the%20visual%20symbol%20of%20the%20crimes%20of%20the%20Nazis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECohen%20draws%20meaning%20from%20her%20tattoo%20in%20that%20it%20signifies%20her%20grandmother%E2%80%99s%20history%20and%20her%20own%20identity%20as%20a%20descendant%20of%20Holocaust%20survivors.%20To%20her%20mind%2C%20replicating%20this%20number%20was%20a%20means%20of%20taking%20her%20grandmother%2C%20as%20a%20person%2C%20and%20her%20legacy%20forward.%20As%20a%20gesture%20and%20an%20indelible%20mark%20she%20carries%20with%20her%2C%20she%20says%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20number%20is%20my%20grandma.%20It%E2%80%99s%20my%20past%2C%20my%20roots%2C%20my%20story.%20It%E2%80%99s%20who%20I%20am.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20potent%20gesture%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Fpdf%2F10.1177%2F07255136211042453%5C%22%3EMy%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%20delves%20into%